      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "of the Arnon.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The latest explorer of Moab says: “Above the Roman bridge are some faint remains of early buildings; perhaps ‘the city that is in the midst of the river.’ At least it is scarcely possible that such exuberant vegetation, with perennial moisture, should have remained unappropriated in the time of Israel’s greatness; and whether the place so vaguely spoken of were above or below the fords;—‘cities’ or villages there were sure to be in the midst of the ‘river’ or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "wady",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".” Tristram’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Land of Moab",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", p. 128.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
