        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of Gad",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] If the view taken above with regard to Aroer is correct, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of Gad",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " must be separated from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the river",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and rendered ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "towards Gad.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Probably some such words as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and they came",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " have dropped out, as the preposition ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "towards",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " before ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jazer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " requires a verb of motion. Indeed there are good reasons for supposing that the Heb. text is corrupt, and that we should read with some MSS. of the Sept.: “And they began from Aroer, and from the city which is in the midst of the ravine; and they came to Gad and towards Jazer.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jazer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Or Jaazer, a city captured by Israel from the Amorites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 21:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), rebuilt by the tribe of Gad (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 32:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 13:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), allotted to the Levites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 21:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), subsequently Moabite (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 16:8-9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and recaptured by Judas Maccabaeus from the Ammonites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Ma 5:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Its site is probably to be placed at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "es Szîr",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", 7 miles W.S.W. of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
